This paper is about natural language generation tasks, specifically paraphrasing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel Seq2Seq model that combines a copying decoder and a restricted generative decoder, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and attention models, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the model's performance in terms of informativeness and language quality, which are metrics commonly used in natural language processing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
